# Documentation Archiving

**Always archive completed work** to `docs/archive/` rather than leaving summary files in repository root.

## File Naming

**Use actual timestamps with seconds-level accuracy:**
```bash
# Get file creation time
stat -c '%y' IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md
# Output: 2025-10-27 02:15:34.123456789 +0000

# Use: 2025-10-27T02-15-34-implementation-summary.md
```

**Format:** `YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS-category-description.md`

**Examples:**
```
2025-10-27T01-17-00-AGENTS.md                 ✓ Actual time
2025-10-27T00-14-34-fix-ingress-and-group.md  ✓ Actual time

2025-10-27T00-00-00-my-summary.md             ✗ BAD - placeholder zeros
```

## What to Archive

✅ Bug fixes - How we fixed X, why we chose approach Y
✅ Feature implementations - What was built, architecture decisions
✅ Investigations - What we learned, recommendations
✅ Debugging findings - Protocol analysis, performance results

## Workflow After Completing Task

```bash
# 1. Archive with proper timestamp
TIMESTAMP=$(stat -c '%y' IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md | cut -d' ' -f1,2 | tr ' ' 'T' | tr ':' '-' | cut -d'.' -f1)
mv "$FILE_TO_ARCHIVE" "docs/archive/${TIMESTAMP}-implementation-summary.md"

# 2. Document key findings (use template from CONTRIBUTING.md)

# 3. Clean up root directory
```

**Template:**
```markdown
# [Title]

**Status**: ✅ Completed
**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD

## Problem
## Root Cause
## Solution
## Files Modified
## Testing
```
